
data owners - Manages access to datasets and ensures policies are consistently enforced.
- Approve or deny access requests, ensure compliance with access policies, and maintain data security.

cdo - Oversees governance frameworks and ensures compliance with regulations like GDPR and HIPAA
-Develops governance frameworks, monitors compliance, and aligns policies with business priorities.

data stewards - Maintains data quality and integrity in assigned domains.
-Perform regular data quality checks, implement standards, and resolve inconsistencies.

it security managers - Manages the company’s data security infrastructure and ensures data is protected against breaches
-Enforces encryption, accesscontrols, and authentication protocols; monitors and resolves security gaps.

Data Protection Officer/Compliance Officer - Under GDPR a dedicated Data Protection Officer is a legal requirement for companies handling large amounts of personal data




Policy 1. 
Gaps - Absence of RBAC and insufficient access review frequency

Improvements - Implement RBAC and conduct quarterly or event-driven access reviews


Policy 2
Gaps - no defined retention schedules

Improvements - Introduce automated retention schedules and deletion protocols aligned with GDPR

Policy 3 

Gaps - Lack of real-time monitoring; no automated tools.

Improvements - Implement automated input validation and real-time quality dashboards


